### -------------------------------------------------------
### REST Client .http file that uses $dotenv syntax
###
### curl-code resolves {{$dotenv VAR}} from a .env file in
### the same directory as this .http file. Place
### rest-client-dotenv.env alongside this file (renamed to
### .env) to test resolution.
###
### Manual test:
### 1. Copy rest-client-dotenv.env to .env in the same dir
### 2. Open this file in VS Code with curl-code active
### 3. Run the first request — URL should resolve to
###    https://httpbin.org/v1/status
### 4. Run the second request — body should contain
###    "source": "manual-import"
### -------------------------------------------------------

### Request using $dotenv variables
GET https://{{$dotenv API_HOST}}/v1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv API_TOKEN}}
X-Request-Id: {{$dotenv REQUEST_PREFIX}}-001

### Mixed: $dotenv + regular environment variables
# Requires an active curl-code environment with host, contentType, version
POST https://{{host}}/v1/data
Authorization: Bearer {{$dotenv API_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "source": "{{$dotenv DATA_SOURCE}}",
    "version": "{{version}}"
}

### $dotenv with missing key (should stay unresolved)
GET https://{{$dotenv API_HOST}}/v1/check
X-Missing: {{$dotenv THIS_KEY_DOES_NOT_EXIST}}

### URL-encoded $dotenv — {{%$dotenv VAR}} syntax
# The DB_CONNECTION value contains special chars (://@) that
# should be percent-encoded when used in a query parameter
GET https://{{$dotenv API_HOST}}/v1/info?conn={{%$dotenv DB_CONNECTION}}&src={{%$dotenv DATA_SOURCE}}
